ENTRY            41788   20251010   20260518   20260518       4228
SUBENT        41788001   20251010   20260518   20260518       4228
BIB                 16        105
TITLE      Measurement of differential and total cross sections
           for 14.1 MeV neutrons on 12C nuclei
AUTHOR     (D.N.Grozdanov,P.S.Prusachenko,N.A.Fedorov,Yu.N.Kopach,
           T.Yu.Tretyakova, G.V.Pampushik, A.V.Andreev, V.R.Skoy,
           C.Hramco, P.G.Filonchik, P.I.Kharlamov, A.L.Barabanov)
           TANGRA collaboration
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/A,61,224,2025)
           #doi:10.1140/epja/s10050-025-01703-5
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB) D.N.Grozdanov,P.S.Prusachenko,N.A.Fedorov,
           Yu.N.Kopach,T.Yu.Tretyakova,G.V.Pampushik,A.V.Andreev,
           V.R.Skoy,C.Hramco, P.G.Filonchik, P.I.Kharlamov,
           A.L.Barabanov
           (3BULBLA) D.N.Grozdanov
           (4RUSMOS) T.Yu.Tretyakova, G.V.Pampushik, A.V.Andreev,
            P.I.Kharlamov
           (4RUSMFT) P.G.Filonchik
           (4RUSMIF) A.L.Barabanov
REL-REF    (I,,P.S.Prusachenko,J,NIM/A,1072,170143,2025)
            Experimental details.
           Detection efficiency curve (exp. and calc.) on Fig.15.
FACILITY   (NGEN,4ZZZDUB) ING-27 neutron generator.
INC-SOURCE (D-T) Tritium sample of copper plate of 2 mm thickness,
           placed at 45 deg angle .
INC-SPECT   EN-RSL-HW = 0.2 MeV was confirmed by N.A.Fedorov.
SAMPLE      Natural graphite plate of 440 x 440 x 21 mm3 size,
           6670+-5 g mass, 1.6505 g/cm3 density, was placed at
           314 mm from the tritium target.
METHOD     (ASSOP) Tagged neutron method.
           (COINC) Alpha-neutron and alpha-gamma coincidences
           (TOF) Time resolution 1.8 nsec (FWHM).
           Measurement with sample and without sample, measurement
           time for both - 25.3 hr.
DETECTOR   (PS) 256-pixel alpha-detector build in ING-27 neutron
           generator. Each pixel of 4 x 4 mm.
           Distance between the center of the alpha-detector and
           the center of the tritium target was 62 mm.
           (SCIN) Detector array of 20 EJ-200 plastic
           scintillators ( rectangular parallelepiped of
           80 x 80 x 300 mm3) was used to detect scattered
           neutrons and gamma-rays.
           Simulated via GEANT4 efficiency of neutron and gammas
           was verified in an additional experiment relative to
           the standard of neutron elastic scattering on hydrogen
           using an additional polyethylene sample directly before
           the main experiment.
CORRECTION For incident neutrons lost in the generator - 8-9 %.
           For low-energy tail of incident neutrons - 1.5 -1.7 %.
           For neutron flux attenuation in sample ( calculated
           using GEANT4 simulation).
           For attenuation and multiple scattering of neutrons and
           gammas in the target and surrounding materials;
           neutron absorption in the sample -
           5-15 % at scattering angle 10-60 and 120-155 degrees,
           20-30 % at angles close to 90 degrees;
           for effect of electro-positron pair production in
           sample and other materials - 10-12 %;
           multiple scattering 3-6 % for (n,n1) channel,
                               5-10 % for (n,n3,4) channels,
                               < 1% for other channels.
           For production of secondary particles for gamma-rays.
           For generation of secondary particles in the target.
           For scattering of gamma-rays and neutrons from detector
           to detector.
           Correction type :
           Apn - attenuation of primary neutrons,
           Asp - attenuation of secondary particles,
           MNS - multiple neutron scattering,
           CTE  - cross talk effect
           Channel      Contribution, %
                        Apn     Asp     MNS     CTE
           gamma        10-11   2-22    10-12   <1
           n0           10-11   2-27    <1      <1
           n1           10-11   2-30    3-6     <1
           n2           10-11   2-33    <1      <1
           n3,4         10-11   2-45    5-10    <1
           n7           10-11   4-48    <1      <1
           The maximum correction value in the range corresponds
           to angles close to 90 degrees.
ANALYSIS   320 (20 detectors and 16 strips) points with different
           angles were obtained for each reaction channel studied.
           The angular distributions were divided into intervals
           of 5 degrees width. For each interval, the weighted
           average value of the angle and differential cross
           section were determined.
           The data are presented in the center-of-mass system,
           except for the angular distribution for gamma-rays.
COMMENT     Of authors:
           1. Besides the 2+ -> 0+ transition in 12C in which
            the 4.439 MeV gamma-rays are emitted the transitions
            in the 13C nuclei as well as the transitions from 1+
            level (12.71 MeV) of 12C nuclei could affect the
            number of detected events in the (n, n gamma) peak.
           2. The obtained data are presented in the
            center-of-mass system,
            except for the angular distribution for gamma-rays
            ( page 223, right column, 3 bottom lines in
              D.N.Grozdanov+,J,EPJ/A,61,224,2025 ).
           3. This work was supported by the RSCF grant
              No. 23-12-00239.
             Of compiler:
            Data of angular distributions received from the author
            ( Subents 006 - 013 ) are given in C.M.S. - confirmed
            by the author N.A.Fedorov.
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by the author N.A.Fedorov.
HISTORY    (20251010C) M.M.
